{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4b75eb4d-6b4a-47d3-8e10-2045c864f59f","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are the main tools and approaches:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` (PrintException) — show the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect specific threads\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows, more powerful):\n- Load SOS: `.loadby sos coreclr`\n- `!pe` — print exception\n- `!clrstack` — managed stack\n- `!analyze -v` — automated crash analysis\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `pe` to check if an unhandled exception caused the crash\n2. Run `clrstack` to see where it happened\n3. If it's a `StackOverflowException` or `AccessViolationException`, check native stacks too\n\nWould you like me to help you run `dotnet-dump analyze` on the file if it's accessible in this environment, or do you need help interpreting specific output?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2ecd55fb-6043-485b-89a6-152e3d1b3099","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n\"USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps for CoreCLR or NativeAOT, capturing dumps from running .NET processes, setting up dump collection in Docker or Kubernetes, using dotnet-dump collect or createdump.\"\n\n\"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing, or for .NET Framework processes.\"\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is explicitly NOT for analyzing dumps. \n\nSince that skill isn't designed for this task, I'll provide direct guidance on how to analyze the dump file instead.","outputTokens":499,"requestId":"5018:1909B6:1FF284F:24816F2:69F555CF"},"id":"108b6f8d-4125-472c-aa6a-040b43a67d06","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:39:41.075Z","parentId":"568c1853-438c-485a-bb0c-139dcd8ca087"}
